               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17300116-23-person213">
                  John 
                  Barrow 
               <interp inst="t17300116-23-person213" type="surname" value="Barrow"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300116-23-person213" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300116-23-person213" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             thus depos'd, I was in the Coffee Room when the Jew came in with Buttons, Buckles , &amp;c. and was going to buy a Pair of Buckles, but was called upon for half a Pint of Wine, after that for some bitter ; when I came again, I see the Prisoner in the Entry putting something in his Bosom; but he drop'd his Glove, I went after him, but he would not readily take it, at last turned himself side-way, and took it; presently the Gentleman miss'd his Sword, and I said, I'll be hang'd if the Jew has not taken it, I run out, and overtook the Prisoner at the end of Hedge-Lane, with the Sword between his Coat and Wastcoat; I laid hold of his Collar, and he begg'd I would let him go, but I took the Sword from him, and brought him back.</p>
               <p>The Prisoner in his Defence, (if it may be called a Defence ) said, that he saw the Sword lying in the Entry just by the Door, stayed a little to see if any Body would own it, and then took it away. The Jury found him <rs id="t17300116-23-verdict131" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17300116-23-verdict131" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17300116-23-verdict131" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder40s"></interp>
               Guilty to the Value of 39 s.
            </rs>
               </p>
